Make sure you have Python 3.8+ installed.

git clone https://github.com/Klodi666/netscan
cd netscan

Scan a subnet (default ports, default threads):
python netscan.py --target 192.168.1.0/24

Scan a single IP with custom ports:
python netscan.py --target 10.0.0.5 --ports 22,80,443

Scan using a file of IPs:
python netscan.py --targets-file targets.txt

Set the number of threads and socket timeout:
python netscan.py --target 192.168.1.0/24 --threads 200 --timeout 1.5

Output

Hosts discovered and their status (UP/DOWN)

Open and closed ports

Captured service banners

Summary of total hosts scanned, ports checked, and open ports found

Color-coded HTML report for easy reading in browsers

Warning ⚠️

Only use NetScan on networks you own or are explicitly authorized to test.

Unauthorized scanning may be illegal in your jurisdiction.

